        <article>
            <p>Managing your monthly expenses can feel overwhelming, but with a few smart strategies, you can keep your finances under control. Here are our top 5 tips:</p>

            <h2>Tip 1: Differentiate Between Needs and Wants</h2>
            <p>One of the easiest ways to cut down on unnecessary spending is by distinguishing between needs (essential expenses) and wants (discretionary expenses).</p>

            <h2>Tip 2: Use the 50/30/20 Rule</h2>
            <p>The 50/30/20 rule is a popular budgeting technique that allocates 50% of your income to needs, 30% to wants, and 20% to savings or debt repayment.</p>

            <h2>Tip 3: Automate Your Savings</h2>
            <p>Set up an automatic transfer to your savings account every month. This way, you’re less likely to spend the money before you have a chance to save it.</p>

            <h2>Tip 4: Reduce Recurring Expenses</h2>
            <p>Review your recurring expenses like subscriptions and memberships. Cancel any services you’re not actively using or can live without.</p>

            <h2>Tip 5: Keep Track of Your Spending</h2>
            <p>Use financial tracking apps or tools to monitor your expenses in real time. This can help you identify areas where you’re overspending and make adjustments quickly.</p>
            
            <p>By following these tips, you’ll be better equipped to manage your monthly expenses and reach your financial goals faster.</p>
